==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roncador
<hw>Ron`ca*dor"</hw> <pr>(r⟦ocr⟧⟦nsm⟧`k⟦adot⟧*d⟦omac⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., a snorer, fr. <ets>roncar</ets> to snore. So
called in allusion to the grunting noise made by them on being taken
from the water. ]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several
species of <state>California</state> sciaenoid food fishes, especially
<spn>Roncador Stearnsi</spn>, which is an excellent market fish, and the
red roncador (<spn>Corvina saturna</spn> syn. <spn>Johnius
saturna</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ronchil</ent>⟦br⟧
